<div class="map-page">
  <section class="hero-section map-hero">
    <div class="hero-content">
      <div class="hero-badge">
        <span class="hero-badge-text">Map MVP</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="hero-title">Map</h1>
      <p class="hero-description">
        Map turns where into a study tool. Follow Paul's journeys, surface key early churches, and
        connect passages to geography without losing the reading-first experience.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="hero-cta primary" href="#mvp-preview">Explore Paul's Journeys</a>
        <a class="hero-cta secondary" href="#map-features">See MVP scope</a>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-stats map-hero-stats">
        <div class="stat">
          <div class="stat-number">4</div>
          <div class="stat-label">Journey routes</div>
          <div class="stat-sublabel">Acts 13-28</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat">
          <div class="stat-number">50+</div>
          <div class="stat-label">Places</div>
          <div class="stat-sublabel">MVP scope</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat">
          <div class="stat-number">8</div>
          <div class="stat-label">Church hubs</div>
          <div class="stat-sublabel">Acts + epistles</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="map-section" id="map-features">
    <div class="map-section-header">
      <div>
        <h2>What the MVP includes</h2>
        <p>
          Start with Paul's journeys and the early church network. Every element is built to
          support reading, not replace it.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="map-badge">MVP Scope</div>
    </div>

    <div class="map-feature-grid">
      <div class="map-feature-card">
        <h3>Journey routes</h3>
        <p>Pick Journey 1-3 or To Rome and step through ordered stops with Acts references.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="map-feature-card">
        <h3>Stop-by-stop focus</h3>
        <p>Use next/previous controls to jump between cities and return to the text in one click.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="map-feature-card">
        <h3>Ancient churches</h3>
        <p>Toggle key communities like Antioch, Corinth, Ephesus, and Rome with profile panels.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="map-feature-card">
        <h3>Chapter-aware defaults</h3>
        <p>Open the map from Acts 13-28 and the relevant stops are already filtered.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="map-feature-card">
        <h3>Modern labels</h3>
        <p>Optional modern place labels keep orientation clear without overwhelming the map.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="map-feature-card">
        <h3>Bookmarkable views</h3>
        <p>Save a place, a journey, or a full map state to revisit later.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="map-section map-entry" id="map-entry">
    <div class="map-section-header">
      <div>
        <h2>Entry points</h2>
        <p>Map lives in the top nav and also appears inside Acts pages for instant context.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="map-entry-grid">
      <div class="map-entry-card">
        <h3>Top nav: Map</h3>
        <p>Start with a focused landing page that defaults to Paul's journeys (MVP).</p>
      </div>
      <div class="map-entry-card">
        <h3>Acts book page</h3>
        <p>Use a dedicated CTA: "View Paul's journeys on Map".</p>
      </div>
      <div class="map-entry-card">
        <h3>Acts chapter pages</h3>
        <p>Open directly to that chapter's places with a filtered stop list.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="map-section map-preview" id="mvp-preview">
    <div class="map-section-header">
      <div>
        <h2>Paul's Journeys (MVP preview)</h2>
        <p>Journey controls, ordered stops, and church markers inside a single workspace.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="map-preview-actions">
        <button class="map-toggle active" type="button" aria-pressed="true">Journeys</button>
        <button class="map-toggle" type="button" aria-pressed="false">Churches</button>
        <button class="map-toggle" type="button" aria-pressed="false">Modern labels</button>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="map-shell">
      <aside class="map-panel">
        <div class="map-panel-header">
          <div>
            <div class="map-kicker">Journey overview</div>
            <h3>Paul's First Journey</h3>
            <p>Acts 13-14 • 13 stops</p>
          </div>
          <div class="map-panel-controls">
            <button class="map-pill active" type="button">Journey 1</button>
            <button class="map-pill" type="button">Journey 2</button>
            <button class="map-pill" type="button">Journey 3</button>
            <button class="map-pill" type="button">To Rome</button>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="map-controls">
          <button class="map-action" type="button">Previous</button>
          <button class="map-action primary" type="button">Play</button>
          <button class="map-action" type="button">Next</button>
        </div>

        <ol class="map-stop-list">
          <li class="map-stop active">
            <div class="map-stop-header">
              <span class="map-stop-name">Antioch (Syria)</span>
              <span class="map-stop-tag">Galatia</span>
            </div>
            <p class="map-stop-ref">Acts 13:1-3</p>
            <div class="map-stop-actions">
              <button class="map-action small" type="button">Read</button>
              <button class="map-action small" type="button">Focus</button>
              <button class="map-action small" type="button">Bookmark</button>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="map-stop">
            <div class="map-stop-header">
              <span class="map-stop-name">Seleucia</span>
              <span class="map-stop-tag">Syria</span>
            </div>
            <p class="map-stop-ref">Acts 13:4</p>
            <div class="map-stop-actions">
              <button class="map-action small" type="button">Read</button>
              <button class="map-action small" type="button">Focus</button>
              <button class="map-action small" type="button">Bookmark</button>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="map-stop">
            <div class="map-stop-header">
              <span class="map-stop-name">Salamis (Cyprus)</span>
              <span class="map-stop-tag">Cyprus</span>
            </div>
            <p class="map-stop-ref">Acts 13:5</p>
            <div class="map-stop-actions">
              <button class="map-action small" type="button">Read</button>
              <button class="map-action small" type="button">Focus</button>
              <button class="map-action small" type="button">Bookmark</button>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ol>

        <div class="map-panel-footer">
          <div class="map-churches-card">
            <h4>Ancient churches</h4>
            <p>Antioch, Corinth, Ephesus, Philippi, Thessalonica, Rome.</p>
            <button class="map-action small" type="button">Browse churches</button>
          </div>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="map-canvas" aria-label="Map canvas preview">
        <div class="map-toolbar">
          <input
            class="map-search"
            type="search"
            placeholder="Search: Ephesus, Galatia, Rome"
            aria-label="Search places or regions"
          />
          <div class="map-toolbar-actions">
            <span class="map-toolbar-pill">Layers</span>
            <span class="map-toolbar-pill">Era: Acts</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="map-canvas-stage">
          <svg class="map-route-svg" viewBox="0 0 600 360" role="img" aria-label="Route preview">
            <path class="map-route-path" d="M120 260 L180 220 L250 210 L320 170 L390 180 L470 140" />
            <circle class="map-route-stop" cx="120" cy="260" r="8" />
            <circle class="map-route-stop" cx="180" cy="220" r="8" />
            <circle class="map-route-stop" cx="250" cy="210" r="8" />
            <circle class="map-route-stop" cx="320" cy="170" r="8" />
            <circle class="map-route-stop" cx="390" cy="180" r="8" />
            <circle class="map-route-stop" cx="470" cy="140" r="8" />
          </svg>
          <div class="map-confident">Confidence: High</div>
          <div class="map-legend">
            <span class="map-legend-item"><span class="map-dot"></span> Journey stops</span>
            <span class="map-legend-item"><span class="map-dot muted"></span> Churches</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="map-section map-next">
    <div class="map-section-header">
      <div>
        <h2>Next after MVP</h2>
        <p>Expand to OT routes, tribal boundaries, and multi-era overlays with confidence labels.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="map-next-grid">
      <div class="map-next-card">
        <h3>OT routes</h3>
        <p>Exodus, exile, and return paths with model variants.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="map-next-card">
        <h3>Tribes by era</h3>
        <p>Timeline slider for shifting tribal territories.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="map-next-card">
        <h3>Empires + provinces</h3>
        <p>Roman, Persian, and Greek overlays with confidence cues.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
